long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1215 ScrollComposite update list real example
There is situation when ScrollComposite must be updated or reseted manualy. I have following scenario:
- I have complex control box with qx.ui.mobile.list.List and few buttons - qx.ui.mobile.list.List inserted in ScrollComposite container - list content is created and updated dynamicaly and number of it's elements may vary - when ScrollComposite is scrolled up and list updated then listed item disappears and there is no way (as I know) to update scroller position to 0 (also I've tried removeAll() and add(list) back to scroller - also no effect)
In attachment some scenario screenshots. I'm proposing to add some methods in qx.ui.mobile.container.ScrollComposite such as resetScrollig() or setScrollingPosition(int).
Thanx.

Fix with: fc143327b746888cc7cc9cfc15c3bff24ca5f8a6
provided the method scrollTo(x,y) for your purpose.
Also made scrollContainer replacable in child classes.

(In reply to comment #1) > Fix with: > fc143327b746888cc7cc9cfc15c3bff24ca5f8a6 > > provided the method scrollTo(x,y) for your purpose. > > Also made scrollContainer replacable in child classes.
Looking good, thanx. Will this fix added to the next release?

Yes of course,
but you can also check out the devel version on GitHub, if it is urgent.
Greetz Christopher

(In reply to comment #3) > Yes of course, > > but you can also check out the devel version on GitHub, if it is urgent. > > Greetz Christopher
Sorry, but I did not understood how to use it. Can you please provide short brief how to scroll qx.ui.mobile.list.List?

Have a look at API doc:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/apiviewer/#qx.ui.mobile.container.ScrollComposite~scrollTo!method_public
You do not scroll the List... you have to scroll the scrollComposite.

(In reply to comment #5) > Have a look at API doc: > > http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/apiviewer/#qx.ui.mobile.container.ScrollComposite~scrollTo!method_public > > You do not scroll the List... you have to scroll the scrollComposite.
So if I need to scroll qx.ui.mobile.list.List how can I get ScrollComposite element from it? As I see it's derived directly from qx.ui.mobile.core.Widget and there is no method to access ScrollComposite element or I've missed something?

(In reply to comment #5)
I've read again my initial post and must apologize for this confusion. Initially I needed to manually scroll qx.ui.mobile.list.List of course. Perhaps I've just copypasted ScrollComposite name from somewhere. That's good you've added scrollTo method to ScrollComposite but I still need to scroll List. Sorry again.

I would wrap the List in a ScrollComposite.
If you want to to trigger a Scroll on parent, just take the method "getLayoutParent()"
Or you can extend the List for beeing automatically wrapped by a scrollComposite.
The list only is not capable to scroll itself.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
